Date: Tue, 23 Aug 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: News agency Strana.ru, 22 Aug 2005
<http://www.strana.ru/news/257371.html>


Foot-and-mouth disease revealed in cows in Khabarovsk region
------------------------------------------------
Quarantine due to detection of foot and mouth disease (FMD) in cows has
been applied in 3 settlements of the Khabarovsk region, informs the
Ministry of Agriculture of the Russian Federation. According to the
message, the diagnosis of FMD, caused by (virus) type Asia-1, has been
confirmed [by tests of samples from the] state farm "Lermontovskiy" in the
Bikinskiy district of the Khabarovsk region (on the border with China),
where suspicion [of such infection] was announced earlier.

According to the Federal Veterinary and Phytosanitary Control Service,
quarantine has been applied in 3 settlements. Experts from the All-Russia
Center [for Control of Animal Health] in Vladimir [have been sent] to the
Khabarovsk region. The press release emphasized that an emergency quantity
of a vaccine containing a component against FMD Asia-1 was delivered.

--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This news item adds some details to the location of the outbreaks, which
might be regarded now as confirmed.

Khabarovsk Krai (1995 pop. 1 588 100 est.) in Russia's Far East lies mostly
in the basin of the lower Amur River but also occupies a vast mountainous
area along the coastline of the Sea of Okhotsk. - Mod.AS]
